sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1407015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It's composed of seven sections:constitutive production of LasR,LasR/PAI1 Inducible promoter with RBS(B0034)and GFP,terminator,constitutive promoter,RhlR protein generator ,RhlR/PAI2 inducible promoter with RBS (B0030) and RFP,Terminator.When PAI1 exsits,the part could be inducibled and expresses GFP protein;When PAI2 exsits,the part could be inducibled and expresses RFP protein.
